### **Q58: How do you handle validation in DTO vs Entity?**

**DTO**: API-level validation (required fields, format, size)
```java
class GoalRequestDTO {
    @NotBlank
    @Size(max = 100)
    private String title;
}
```

**Entity**: Database-level validation (unique constraints, relationships)
```java
@Entity
class Goal {
    @Column(unique = true)
    private String code;
}
```

DTO validates incoming data. Entity enforces database rules. Two different concerns.

