### **Q59: In microservices, should DTOs be shared across services?**

No! Each service should have its own DTOs.

Bad practice: Common DTO library that all services import. Creates tight coupling. If one service changes DTO, all services need to update.

Good practice: Each service defines its own DTOs. If Service A calls Service B, it uses Service B's API contract but may convert to its own internal DTOs.

This is the microservice philosophy - independence over reusability.

