### **Q60: How would you implement DAO layer in PerformanceTrack?**

In Spring Boot, you don't need traditional DAO. Use repositories:

```java
interface GoalRepository extends JpaRepository<Goal, Long> {
    List<Goal> findByEmployeeId(Long empId);
    List<Goal> findByStatus(String status);
}
```

If you need complex queries, add custom repository:

```java
interface GoalRepositoryCustom {
    List<Goal> findGoalsWithComplexCriteria(...);
}

class GoalRepositoryImpl implements GoalRepositoryCustom {
    @PersistenceContext
    private EntityManager em;
    
    public List<Goal> findGoalsWithComplexCriteria(...) {
        // custom query
    }
}
```

This is the modern DAO pattern in Spring Boot.

